oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Postcard photograph of James Knox Moore
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Moore pictured at dedication of Confederate monument on courthouse square in Shelbyville, Tenn. The monument reads, in part, "In memory of the 'Shelbyville Rebels' Co. F. 41st Tenn. Reg't. C.S.A. and all soldiers from Bedford County who fought for the Confederacy in the War Between the States 1861-1865." Moore served as a trooper in Co. C, 6th Miss. Cav. Regt., CSA
